-- Burgan Bank of Kuwait Plans to Sell Dollar Bonds, Appoints Sale Managers
-- B y   F i o n a   M a c D o n a l d
-- 2010-09-22T07:10:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/burgan-bank-of-kuwait-plans-to-sell-10-year-lower-tier-2-bonds-in-dollars.html
Burgan Bank  plans to sell bonds in
U.S. dollars and appointed JPMorgan Chase & Co., Morgan Stanley
and Standard Chartered Plc to manage the sale, the Kuwaiti
lender said today.  Kipco Asset Management Co. was named joint-director for the
issue, the bank said in a statement to the Kuwait Stock
Exchange. Burgan Bank shareholders in June approved the sale of
as much as 140 million dinars ($489 million) of debt.  To contact the reporter on this story:
